Re: Reading/Writing Blocks and FLATDATA

Bitcointalk

2010-07-24 04:04:20 UTC - [11]Original Post

   FLATDATA was a workaround to serialize a fixed field length array.
   There was a cleaner way to make it understand how to serialize arrays
   directly, but MSVC6 couldnʼt do it and I wanted to keep compatibility
   with MSVC6 at that time.  We donʼt support MSVC6 anymore because we use
   something in Boost that doesnʼt.  We lost support for it after 0.2.0.
   Maybe someday Iʼll swap in the clean way that just knows how to
   serialize fixed length arrays without wrapping them in FLATDATA.
